This paper proposes a method to improve the variational posterior distribution in variational auto-encoders (VAE) using a volume-preserving flow. The paper focuses on empirical evaluation of the proposed method on MNIST dataset and histopathology data. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the use of the proposed method in neural engineering (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY), but these are not the main focus of the paper.
